ASSEMBLY JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging Congress to enact
legislation to prohibit officers and agents of the United
States Immigration and Customs Enforcement in the
United States Department of Homeland Security from
entering schools and places of worship for the purposes of
enforcing federal immigration laws.
1 WHEREAS, All children in the United States are entitled to equal
2 access to a public elementary and secondary education, regardless of
3 their or their parents’ actual or perceived national origin, citizenship
4 or immigration status; and
5 WHEREAS, Places of worship have historically been viewed as
6 sacred and protected spaces for persons who attend religious
7 services to exercise their religious beliefs and attend religious
8 services and offer various resources to support and protect anyone in
9 need; and
10 WHEREAS, Educational personnel and members of religious
11 organizations are often primary sources of support, resources and
12 information to assist and support students and persons who attend
13 religious services; and
-
