1 WHEREAS, The activities of federal immigration law
2 enforcement agencies, on or around schools and places of worship,
3 including, without limitation, surveillance, interviews, demands for
4 information, arrests, detention or any other federal immigration
5 enforcement activities, harmfully disrupt the learning and religious
6 environments of schools and places of worship and significantly
7 interfere with the ability of students and persons who attend
8 religious services, regardless of their immigration status, to access
9 free public education and places of worship; now, therefore, be it
10 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY AND SENATE OF THE STATE OF
11 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the members of the 83rd Session of the
12 Nevada Legislature hereby urge Congress to enact legislation to
13 prohibit officers and agents of the United States Immigration and
14 Customs Enforcement in the United States Department of Homeland
15 Security from entering schools and places of worship for the
16 purposes of upholding federal immigration laws; and be it further
17 RESOLVED, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly prepare and
18 transmit a copy of this resolution to the Vice President of the United
19 States as the presiding officer of the United States Senate, the
20 Speaker of the United States House of Representatives and each
21 member of the Nevada Congressional Delegation; and be it further
22 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
23 passage.
